    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
        }
        .chart-container {
            position: relative;
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 600px;
            margin-left: auto;
            margin-right: auto;
            height: 320px;
            max-height: 400px;
        }
        @media (min-width: 768px) {
            .chart-container {
                height: 400px;
            }
        }
        .component-card.active {
            transform: translateY(-5px);
            box-shadow: 0 10px 15px -3px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1), 0 4px 6px -2px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
            border-color: #0d9488;
        }
        .diagram-node {
            transition: all 0.3s ease-in-out;
        }
        .diagram-node:hover {
            transform: scale(1.05);
        }
        .diagram-line {
            position: absolute;
            background-color: #9ca3af;
            transform-origin: 0 0;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body class="bg-stone-50 text-stone-800">
    <!-- Chosen Palette: Calm Neutrals -->
    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application is designed as a single-page, focused dashboard to facilitate deep understanding of a complex topic. The structure avoids traditional navigation, instead using an interactive, exploratory model. It starts with a high-level introduction, then encourages users to dive into the three core components via clickable cards. This prevents information overload. A visual diagram then contextualizes the Promise within the broader TML framework, and a final interactive chart provides a powerful visual metaphor for its impact. This user-driven flow from 'what' to 'how' to 'why' is more effective for learning than a linear document. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
